DataElement.preferredName: Investigator Study Protocol Contact Person Status Date Range ISO21090.IVL.TS.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An individual who conducts scientific research. In a clinical setting this individual actually conducts and/or supervises the clinical investigation and study-related procedures.  The investigator monitors the safety of the trial subjects and investigational staff (under whose immediate direction an agent is administered or dispensed to a subject).  The investigator collects and analyses data and study documents, and provides reports in compliance with applicable requirements.:A detailed examination, analysis, or critical inspection of a subject designed to discover facts about it.:A rule which guides how an activity should be performed.:A person acting as a channel for communication on behalf of a group._A condition or state at a particular time.:The particular day, month and year an event has happened or will happen.:The difference between the lowest and highest numerical values; the limits or scale of variation._Set of consecutive values of an ordered base datatype of the type TS.
